\subsection{Dual-Layer Difficulty Adaptation}
A key innovation decouples UI responsiveness from the heavier multi-agent pipeline. The \textbf{Synchronous Layer} applies a deterministic rule-based mapping immediately upon answer submission: if correct, Easy$\rightarrow$Medium, Medium$\rightarrow$Hard, Hard$\rightarrow$Hard; if incorrect, Hard$\rightarrow$Medium, Medium$\rightarrow$Easy, Easy$\rightarrow$Easy. The next question is generated at this difficulty and returned in the JSON response for sub-second UI updates. The \textbf{Asynchronous Layer} spawns a daemon thread running the full SOLMA$\rightarrow$SOLPA$\rightarrow$SOLTA CrewAI pipeline. The AI analysis is persisted to \texttt{QuestionPerformance} and \texttt{AdaptiveLearningHistory}, and \texttt{final\_difficulty} is updated. The thread closes its DB connection in a \texttt{finally} block to prevent leaks.

