\subsection{Agent Role Separation and Pipeline Integrity}
The three-agent design enforces a separation of concerns that directly mirrors the APOT model's staged reasoning \cite{outay2024}. The SOLMA agent (Evaluator) handles only factual comparison, ensuring correctness determination is isolated from any difficulty reasoning. The SOLPA agent (Predictor) applies psychometric heuristics exclusively to the current question, without considering adaptation goals. The SOLTA agent (Overseer) alone integrates correctness, difficulty prediction, and adaptive rules to produce actionable transition recommendations. This staged design prevents conflation of concerns and makes each agent's reasoning independently auditable. Table~\ref{tab:agent_roles} summarizes the mapping.

